15: // [#protodoc-title: Aggregated Discovery Service (ADS)]
16: 
17: // Discovery services for endpoints, clusters, routes,
18: // and listeners are retained in the package `envoy.api.v2` for backwards
19: // compatibility with existing management servers. New development in discovery
20: // services should proceed in the package `envoy.service.discovery.v2`.
21: 
22: // See https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy-api#apis for a description of the role of
23: // ADS and how it is intended to be used by a management server. ADS requests
24: // have the same structure as their singleton xDS counterparts, but can
25: // multiplex many resource types on a single stream. The type_url in the
26: // DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse provides sufficient information to recover
27: // the multiplexed singleton APIs at the Envoy instance and management server.
