  "text": "## xDS Configuration Discovery Service Flow\n\n### Overview\nThe xDS configuration discovery flow is a bidirectional gRPC streaming mechanism where Envoy (data plane) client subscribes to configuration resources from a control plane server. The flow involves three main components:\n\n### 1. Control Plane Server (go-control-plane)\n\n**Proto Definitions (data-plane-api):**\n- `github.com/sg-evals/data-plane-api--84e84367:envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads.proto` defines the `AggregatedDiscoveryService` with two main RPCs:\n  - `rpc StreamAggregatedResources(stream DiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DiscoveryResponse)`\n  - `rpc DeltaAggregatedResources(stream DeltaDiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DeltaDiscoveryResponse)`\n\n- `github.com/sg-evals/data-plane-api--84e84367:envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto` defines the core message types:\n  - `DiscoveryRequest`: Contains `version_info`, `node`, `resource_names`, `type_url`, `response_nonce`, and `error_detail`\n  - `DiscoveryResponse`: Contains `version_info`, `resources` (list of google.protobuf.Any), `type_url`, `nonce`, and `control_plane`\n  - `DeltaDiscoveryRequest` and `DeltaDiscoveryResponse` for incremental updates\n\n**Server Implementation (go-control-plane):**\n- `github.com/sg-evals/go-control-plane--71637ad6:pkg/server/v3/server.go::StreamAggregatedResources` (line 189) is the main gRPC handler that receives incoming discovery requests and sends responses\n- `github.com/sg-evals/go-control-plane--71637ad6:envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads_grpc.pb.go` contains the generated gRPC service definitions for `AggregatedDiscoveryServiceServer` and `AggregatedDiscoveryServiceClient`\n- `github.com/sg-evals/go-control-plane--71637ad6:envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.pb.go` contains the generated Go structs for `DiscoveryRequest` (line 210) and `DiscoveryResponse` (line 345)\n\n### 2. Data Plane Client (Envoy)\n\n**Subscription Management:**\n- `github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2:source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h` defines the `GrpcSubscriptionImpl` class (line 20) which adapts the typed Subscription interface to the untyped GrpcMux\n- `github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2:source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.cc::GrpcSubscriptionImpl::start()` (line 32) initiates the subscription by calling `grpc_mux_->addWatch()` with the type_url and resource names\n\n**Mux Layer:**\n- `github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2:envoy/config/grpc_mux.h` defines the abstract `GrpcMux` interface with methods:\n  - `start()`: Initiates stream with management server\n  - `addWatch()`: Starts a configuration subscription for specific resources\n  - `onDiscoveryResponse()`: Handles received discovery responses\n- The concrete implementations in `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h` and `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.h` manage the actual bidirectional stream using the gRPC async client\n\n**Base Templates:**\n- `github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2:source/common/config/subscription_base.h` provides a template-based subscription callback implementation\n\n### Configuration Update Flow\n\n1. **Subscription Initiation**: Envoy's `GrpcSubscriptionImpl::start()` calls `grpc_mux_->addWatch()` registering interest in resources of a specific type_url (e.g., type.googleapis.com/envoy.config.cluster.v3.Cluster)\n\n2. **Request Transmission**: The gRPC mux establishes a bidirectional stream to the control plane using the `StreamAggregatedResources` RPC and sends the initial `DiscoveryRequest` containing:\n   - `type_url`: The resource type being requested\n   - `resource_names`: List of specific resource names (empty means request all resources)\n   - `node`: Node information identifying the Envoy instance\n   - `version_info`: Version of last accepted configuration\n\n3. **Request Reception**: Control plane's `StreamAggregatedResources` handler receives the `DiscoveryRequest` and queries its configuration cache for matching resources\n\n4. **Response Generation**: Control plane sends `DiscoveryResponse` containing:\n   - `resources`: List of google.protobuf.Any messages containing typed resource configurations\n   - `type_url`: Matching the request type_url\n   - `version_info`: New version of this resource set\n   - `nonce`: Unique identifier for this response\n\n5. **Response Processing**: Envoy's GrpcMux receives the response through `onDiscoveryResponse()`, decodes the resources using the registered OpaqueResourceDecoder, and calls the subscription callbacks with the decoded resources\n\n6. **ACK/NACK**: Envoy sends back a `DiscoveryRequest` with the same nonce and updated `version_info` to ACK the update, or includes `error_detail` to NACK\n\n7. **Delta Updates**: For incremental updates, the Delta RPC (`DeltaAggregatedResources`) uses `DeltaDiscoveryRequest` with `resource_names_subscribe`/`resource_names_unsubscribe` and `DeltaDiscoveryResponse` with only changed/removed resources\n\n### Key Type URLs\n\nCommon resource types that flow through this system:\n- `type.googleapis.com/envoy.config.listener.v3.Listener` (LDS)\n- `type.googleapis.com/envoy.config.cluster.v3.Cluster` (CDS)\n- `type.googleapis.com/envoy.config.route.v3.RouteConfiguration` (RDS)\n- `type.googleapis.com/envoy.config.endpoint.v3.ClusterLoadAssignment` (EDS)\n\nThe ADS (Aggregated Discovery Service) allows multiplexing all these resource types on a single bidirectional stream, identified by the `type_url` field in each request/response."
}

